## ğŸ”¹ What is the difference?

| Method      | `driver.close()`                   | `driver.quit()`                           |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ’¥ Action   | Closes **only the current tab**    | Shuts down **all tabs/windows + session** |
| ğŸŒ Scope    | Active browser tab/window only     | Whole browser session, driver, memory     |
| ğŸ’¾ Memory   | Keeps WebDriver session alive      | Ends WebDriver session completely         |
| ğŸ§  Use Case | If you're done with *just one* tab | If you're done with the *entire* test     |
| ğŸš¨ Risk     | Can cause memory leaks if overused | You lose session if done too early        |

---

## ğŸ” Why the difference matters?

| Scenario                                      | What to use                            |
| --------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Test involves **multiple tabs** (popups)?     | Use `close()` for closing just one tab |
| Done with **all** browser interactions?       | Use `quit()` to fully exit everything  |
| You want to **reuse driver** in another test? | Donâ€™t `quit()` â€” it kills the session  |

---

## ğŸ”§ When to use?

### âœ… `driver.close()`

Use when:

* You opened a **new window or tab** (e.g. ad popup, child window)
* You want to close it after action and return to the main one

```java
driver.switchTo().window(childWindowId);
driver.close(); // Only closes that tab
driver.switchTo().window(parentWindowId);
```

---

### âœ… `driver.quit()`

Use when:

* Your test is **completely over**
* You want to **release resources** (memory, sockets, processes)
* Youâ€™re exiting from a **test suite**

```java
driver.quit(); // Ends everything, good night ğŸ’¤
```

---

## ğŸ§ª Code Demo (Real-World)

```java
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
driver.get("https://example.com");

// Opens another tab/window
String mainWindow = driver.getWindowHandle();
Set<String> allWindows = driver.getWindowHandles();

for (String window : allWindows)
{
    if (!window.equals(mainWindow))
    {
        driver.switchTo().window(window);
        driver.close();  // Closes only the new tab
    }
}

driver.switchTo().window(mainWindow);
// Do more work, then finally:
driver.quit(); // Cleans up fully
```

